      "content": "Wait, isolated segment? I didn't see any mention of network isolation in the initial scan report or the architecture overview. Are you sure about that? If that segment isn't actually air-gapped from the main database, a \"surgical patch\" won't do much once someone's already in. Can you double check the network topology logs and confirm that isolation is 100% there? I don't want to skip a shutdown if we're actually exposed.",
